				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I disagree with buying only one arrow.  There have been times where I have needed to wait a long time for a Rez.  Instead of sitting aroung nekkid I loot everything but my 1 arrow.  Then I can pull 1 more arrow of the stack and equip it so I can keep killing stuff.  If I have to abandon the corpse, I still have arrows to Equip and am only out 1 arrow.
<br />

<br />
I have occasionally died unexpectedly on Plane of Sky raids, when I do, I purposely leave a corpse in the zone by not looting my arrow.  I am only keyed to the 4th Island, and if we go to island 5 and I don't have a key, I would rather they summon an existing corpse instead of having to make a fresh one.  If I only had 1 arrow, I would have to leave some other piece of equipment behind.  If I have planned the death, I usually put some foraged roots in an inventory slot to leave on the corpse.
<br />

<br />
That being said, I have a stack of the Mithril Champion (Fire damage) arrows, a stack of Shadow Tipped (Magic Damage) arrows, and a stack of Ice Tipped (Cold Damage) arrows.  I have only lost 2 arrows so far.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=960246" target="_blank" class="postlink">Khojah</a>
